w:r.w:t: Welcome to the Department of Computer Science & Business Systems

Welcome to a department that blends the power of technology with the world of business. Here, you'll gain a strong foundation in computer science while also learning how to apply your technical skills to solve real-world business challenges.

The Computer Science & Business Systems program focuses on the integration of IT and business management. Students are equipped with the knowledge to design, develop, and implement technology solutions to support business operations, improve decision-making, and drive innovation. The curriculum covers core computer science subjects such as software development, databases, cybersecurity, and data analytics, while also providing insights into business management, marketing, finance, and operations.

Graduates of this program are prepared for careers in both technology and business, including roles such as business systems analyst, software developer, IT consultant, project manager, and data scientist. The combination of technical expertise and business acumen
a wide range of opportunities in industries such as IT consulting, finance, e-commerce, and enterprise software.
To provide competent learning ecosystem to develop the understanding of technology and business to produce innovative, principled and insightful leaders to meet the societal demands.
Department of Computer Science and Business Systems shall,
To deliver high-quality education in the fields of technology and business through effective teaching-learning practices and a conducive learning environment.
To create the center of excellence through collaborations with industries and various entities, addressing the evolving demands of society.
To foster an environment that promotes innovation, multidisciplinary research, skill enhancement and entrepreneurship.
To uphold and advocate for elevated standards of professional ethics and transparency.
ONE DAY WORKSHOP ON CO, PO & MAPPING

Science and Business Systems had organized One Day Workshop on "CO, PO and Mapping" for the teaching staff of KSSEM on 11/05/2024. School of Engineering and Management organized a session on "Innovation/Prototype Validation - Converting Innovation into Start-up" on 29th August 2025 for 5th and 7th semester students. The session was delivered by Mr. Krishna Bhargav K L, Assistant Professor, Department of MBA, KSSEM, Bengaluru.
The Department of Computer Science and Business

established with an intake of 60 in the year 2022. The Department offers 4 years of B.E program to promote excellence in producing Industry perspective professionals. This course is designed by TCS and has been approved by AICTE to provide Industry 4.0 ready professionals who add more value to the organization.
The students are also exposed to emerging topics such as Analytics, Deep
, Machine Learning, Cloud Computing, Internet of Things and Design thinking to enable
to welcome you to the Department of Computer Science and Business Systems.

Given the high demand for Computer Science professionals from the industry, the College has launched a new four undergraduate industry relevant Computer Science and Business Systems (CSBS) program powered by Tata Consultancy Services to address the growing need of engineering talent with managerial skills.

This curriculum aims to ensure that the students graduating from the program not only know the core topics of Computer Science but also develop an equal appreciation of Humanities, Management Sciences, and Human Values.
The students are also exposed to pursue Higher Studies in Reputed Universities Abroad and India with varied specializations and to become a successful Entrepreneur in the IT
domain with Innovative Business Skills acquired through the competent curriculum designed by TCS.
Active mentoring by Expert faculty members.
Dual Course which includes Technical & Management Studies which is the need of the hour.
Higher chances of placement as TCS have promised to prefer CSBS.
Strong in Ethics and Life Values
Bachelor of Engineering (B.E.) in Computer Science and Business Systems (CS&BS) with approved intake of 60 students and a lateral entry of 20% from 2nd year.

health and safety, and the cultural, societal, and environmental considerations.

, health, safety, legal, and cultural issues and the consequent responsibilities relevant to

Function effectively as an individual, and as a member or leader in teams, and in multidisciplinary settings.
Communicate effectively with the engineering community and with society at large. Be able to comprehend and write effective reports documentation. Make effective

Demonstrate knowledge and understanding of engineering and management principles and apply these to one's own work, as a member and leader in a team. Manage projects in multidisciplinary environments.
have the preparation and ability to engage in independent and life-long learning in the broadest context of technological change.
Graduates of B.E. program in Computer Science and Business Systems will be able
Pursue a prosperous professional journey in Information Technology and its related industries.
Creating innovative engineering solutions through continual learning, research and advanced problem-solving skills.
Comprehend fundamental and advanced concepts within the core domains of Computer Science to analyze, design and implement optimal solutions for real-world challenges.
Grasp business principles and employ the latest technologies to address business challenges effectively.

The faculty of CS & BS department attends various MOOCS and training programs on advanced topics, updates their knowledge and skills, and gives additional inputs in the classes. Further, the faculty conducts various innovative teaching and learning activities to engage the students effectively and efficiently, which
Teaching with live demo sessions, working models, simulations and animated videos
Assignments which include mini projects and case studies
Conduction of online and classroom quizzes, surprise class tests, open book assignments, group discussions, seminars etc.
Usage of ICT, Pupil pod and Google classrooms for posting assignments and lecture materials
Usage of Google forms and Kahoot for online interaction, assessment and evaluation
The instructional materials are uploaded in Google Drive and are made available on institutional websites for student and faculty access.

Internships are foundational in preparing students for the workforce and providing opportunities after graduation. Most employers seek career-ready college graduates who have been equipped with prior experiences and skills
field. An internship is important because it can present you with new skills and opportunities that

would not receive otherwise. Interns not only gain technical knowledge within the industry of their choice, but they also learn how to interact with professionals in a workplace setting, and develop essential soft skills like time management, organization, adaptability, problem-solving and teamwork. An internship is the best way to gain work experience as a student. Internships give you the valuable practical experience needed along with theoretical knowledge. Employers often note that there is a disconnect between the requirements of the industry and the academics. This gap can be bridged by an internship and pitch you as an ideal candidate.
